<h2>MH Executive Director is guest on CONTEXT with Lorna Dueck</h2>
</div>
<p></p>
<p>11.20.13</p>
<div class="newsbody"><p>On Tuesday Nov. 19, Matthew House Executive Director Anne Woolger ( left ) was a guest on the current events program CONTEXT with Lorna Dueck.&nbsp; She spoke on the topic of Canada&#39;s response to refugees.&nbsp; Anne was interviewed along with several other refugee rights activists including Janet Dench, Director of the Canadian Council for Refugees and Mary Jo Leddy, Romero House, toronto Director. A former resident of Matthew House from Congo was also featured. The exact date when the program will be broadcast will be announced shortly.<img alt="" src="/site/ywd_trialsite_1564/assets/images/Context,_Anne_with_Lorna_Dueck,_Nov._19,2013.jpg" style="width: 998px; height: 768px;" /></p></div>
